attributeList.attribute: Tethering complexes which provide the initial recognition event that links a particular vesicle with its target membrane. Participates in intra-Golgi and endosome-Golgi transport. Binds to a component of the COPI coat. BET3, BET5, TRS23, and TRS31 create a catalytic site for promoting GDP/GTP exchange in YPT1.

The estimated size of TRAPPII is most consistent with the formation of a stable dimeric complex. EMD studies suggest that the nine TRAPPII components form a core complex that dimerizes into a three-layered, diamond-shaped structure. The three TRAPPII-specific subunits cap the ends and form the middle layer responsible for dimerization.
